    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The concrete actor adds building influence in an area of 3x3 cells starting with the infantry's cell as top left corner. If you offset the spawning cells of the terrain now to anywhere outside of those 3x3 cells with the influence of the dummy concrete actor, the check will fail because `GetBuildingAt(c)` is not `self`, but `null` instead. However (judging by the comment as well), placing the tiles on `null` should be entirely fine.\r\n\r\nEdit: Image for further illustration:\r\n![d2kconcrete](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7704140/24060036/be0c83e4-0b51-11e7-99a7-659145c2acad.png)"
  },
